		<div style="float: left; clear: both; margin-top: 10px;">
			<p style="text-align: center; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 40px; font-size: 14px;"><strong>Aishaudio.com &ndash; Bios on Some of Our Most Popular Speakers</strong></p>                        
			<p><b>Rabbi Motty Berger</b> is noted for his lucid and compelling approach to “hot” issues, including evolution, faith in God, anti-semitism and suffering. A frequent guest lecturer in cities around the world, Rabbi Berger’s ability to convey Torah wisdom to current events makes him one of Aish HaTorah’s most popular speakers.</p><br />
  			<p><b>Rabbi Yitzchak Berkowitz</b> is a widely respected teacher with a unique ability to present a wide range of Jewish thought and practice in the most clear and understandable manner. The author of two books on Shmiras Haloshon (the practice of positive speech), Rabbi Berkowitz has taught and counseled thousands of students, from novices to ordained Rabbis.</p><br />
  			<p><b>Rebbetzin Tziporah Heller</b> is an outstanding scholar, author, weekly columnist and gifted lecturer. Her keen wit and profound knowledge are apparent in her audio classes, including her popular series on the role of women in Judaism and the lives of women in the Bible.</p><br />
  			<p><b>Rabbi Ari Kahn</b> combines the mystical explorations of Kabbalah and chassidic thought with a broad approach to Torah study that includes psychology, literature and history. The Director of Foreign Student Programs at Bar Ilan University and a senior lecturer at Aish HaTorah, Rabbi Kahn lectures frequently in the U.S., England, and South Africa. He is the author of two books and writes a weekly commentary on the Bible.</p><br />
  			<p><b>Rabbi Zev Leff</b> is a renowned lecturer and educator, noted for his ability to present the most difficult concepts in a very clear, precise way. The Rosh Yeshiva became the guiding light of Moshav Mattityahu in Israel after building a thriving Jewish community through his pulpit in North Miami Beach. He the author of "Shiurei Bina - Outlooks &amp; Insights on the Weekly Torah Portion".</p><br />
  			<p><b>Dr. David Luchins</b> is the Chairman of Political Science at Touro College in New York and was the Senior Advisor to former U.S. Senator Pat Moynihan for 20 years. With his great humor and vast knowledge of politics and history, he always provides insightful and provocative classes.</p><br />
  			<p><b>Rabbi Noach Orlowek</b> is acclaimed as an expert educator, counselor, and speaker. He offers Torah wisdom coupled with his vast experience in child rearing and counseling to deliver fascinating classes. The author of several books, Rabbi Orlowek is mashgiach in Yeshivas Torah Ohr.</p><br />
  			<p><b>Mrs. Lori Palatnik</b> is a writer and educator, who regularly lectures in the United States and Canada. The author of several books, she has an ability to inspire her audiences with the power that classic Jewish wisdom has to give meaning to modern life. She regularly counsels individuals and families dealing with the loss of a loved one, and leads a group of women to tour Israel every summer.</p><br />
			<p><b>Rabbi Zelig Pliskin</b> is the author of more than a dozen self-development books, including Love Your Neighbor; Guard Your Tongue, and Marriage. He is a popular Aish HaTorah lecturer around the world, as well as a marriage and guidance counselor. Rabbi Pliskin eagerly shares his expertise in neuro-linguistic programming to help people develop the fine character traits loved by the Jewish tradition.</p><br />
			<p><b>Rebbetzin Denah Weinberg’s</b> deep knowledge of Jewish wisdom and her belief in every Jew’s greatness are apparent in her classes. She is the Dean of E.Y.A.H.T., Aish HaTorah's College for Women, where she has influenced hundreds of women to maximize their potential for greatness.</p><br />		
			<p><b>Rabbi Noah Weinberg</b> is the Dean and Founder of Aish HaTorah International. A leader in the movement to bring the wisdom of Judaism to all Jews, regardless of their background, Rabbi Weinberg has built an organization in 30 years that touches the lives of more than 100,000 people every year in 28 cities around the world. His best selling “48 Ways” is a powerful series of tools to help people get the most out of life.</p><br />
			<p>Until his death in 1999, <b>Rabbi Yaakov Weinberg zt"l</b> was Rosh Yeshiva of Ner Yisroel, one of the U.S.’s most prestigious yeshivas. For more than 50 years, Rabbi Weinberg taught in various capacities at the college and traveled the world imparting his wisdom to thousands of eager listeners. He is the older brother and mentor of Rabbi Noah Weinberg, the dean and founder of Aish HaTorah.</p>
